# **4\. Group 3 — Code Node Changes (3 Nodes)**

The three Build Call code nodes currently embed system prompt content inside JavaScript template literals. This is architecturally incorrect — system prompts are behavioral instructions, not data logic, and must live in the OpenAI node. The code node's role is data assembly only.

## **4.1 Why This Change Is Required**

When a full multi-section system prompt (voice rules, field definitions, guardrails, examples, output contract) is embedded in a JS template literal, every editorial change to the prompt requires opening a code node, navigating template syntax, managing escape characters, and risking breakage to surrounding data logic. That is the wrong tool for that job.

Once system prompts live in the OpenAI node's System Message field, prompt refinement is a pure text edit — open the node, update the copy, save. No code risk, no escaping, no logic to break.

## **4.2 Changes Required — All Three Nodes**

Apply identically to: Code: Build Call 1 Prompt, Code: Build Call 2 Prompt, Code: Build Call 3 Prompt

| REMOVE: The entire 'const systemPrompt \= \`...\`' block from each node. Delete from the opening backtick to the closing backtick and semicolon. |
| :---- |

| REMOVE: The callN\_system\_prompt key from each node's return object. The return should no longer include this field. |
| :---- |

| KEEP: Everything else. The data assembly logic, the user prompt construction, all input references, all passthrough fields. Only the system prompt variable and its return key are removed. |
| :---- |

