# **7\. Chain Integrity — Confirmed, No Changes Required**

The sequential dependency chain across all three GPT calls is structurally sound. No modifications needed. This section documents the confirmed patterns for reference.

## **7.1 How Call 2 Accesses Call 1 Output**

Code: Build Call 2 Prompt references two upstream nodes:

* $('Code: Build Call 1 Prompt').first().json — retrieves the full input data payload (scores, stage, capabilities) assembled before Call 1 fired

* $('Code: Parse Call 1 \+ Build Rows').all() — retrieves the parsed Call 1 GPT outputs, specifically call1Items\[0\].json.\_call1\_parsed

This pattern is correct. n8n retains all node outputs in memory for the duration of a workflow run. The cross-reference to the parse node is valid regardless of what the Supabase write node does with the data downstream.

## **7.2 How Call 3 Accesses Input Data**

Code: Build Call 3 Prompt references only $('Code: Build Call 1 Prompt').first().json for its full input data — including all\_capabilities (the 25-item array), top\_leverage\_capabilities, top\_strengths\_capabilities, and stage context. This is correct. Call 3 does not need Call 2's outputs to do its job.

## **7.3 Partial Write Run Nodes**

Supabase: Partial Write Run — After Call 1 and After Call 2 update the gm\_gpt\_runs record with run status progression (running\_call\_2, running\_call\_3). These nodes reference gpt\_run\_id via $('Code: Build Call 1 Prompt') and $('Code: Build Call 2 Prompt') respectively. Both references are correct and will continue to work after the code node changes in Group 3\.

